    {
      "id": "el_17",
      "type": "text",
      "x": 535,
      "y": 419,
      "width": 367,
      "height": 172,
      "text": "Age difference stays CONSTANT always\nSum of ages increases by 2t after t years\n\nIf ratio A:B = m:n, diff = d:\n  A = m.d/(m-n), B = n.d/(m-n)\n\nRatio was m:n, becomes p:q after t yrs:\n  (mk+t)/(nk+t) = p/q -> solve for k\n\nFather age when son born = their age difference\n\"1/3 more\" means multiply by 4/3 (NOT 1/3 of)",
      "fontSize": 13,
      "fontFamily": 3,
      "textAlign": "left",
      "verticalAlign": "top",
      "baseline": 13,
      "strokeColor": "#1e1e1e",
      "backgroundColor": "transparent",
      "fillStyle": "solid",
      "strokeWidth": 1,
      "roughness": 0,
      "opacity": 100,
      "angle": 0,
      "seed": 1700,
      "version": 1,
      "versionNonce": 17,
      "isDeleted": false,
      "boundElements": null,
      "updated": 1,
      "link": null,
      "locked": false,
      "groupIds": [
        "f4"
      ],
      "containerId": null,
      "originalText": "Age difference stays CONSTANT always\nSum of ages increases by 2t after t years\n\nIf ratio A:B = m:n, diff = d:\n  A = m.d/(m-n), B = n.d/(m-n)\n\nRatio was m:n, becomes p:q after t yrs:\n  (mk+t)/(nk+t) = p/q -> solve for k\n\nFather age when son born = their age difference\n\"1/3 more\" means multiply by 4/3 (NOT 1/3 of)",
      "autoResize": true,
      "lineHeight": 1.2,
      "strokeStyle": "solid",
      "frameId": null,
      "roundness": null
    },
