      "originalText": "Cube: V=a^3, TSA=6a^2, diag=a.sqrt3\nCuboid: V=lbh, TSA=2(lb+bh+lh)\nCylinder: V=pi.r^2.h, CSA=2.pi.r.h, TSA=2.pi.r(r+h)\nCone: V=1/3.pi.r^2.h, l=sqrt(r^2+h^2), CSA=pi.r.l\nSphere: V=4/3.pi.r^3, SA=4.pi.r^2\nHemisphere: V=2/3.pi.r^3, TSA=3.pi.r^2\n\nFrustum: V=(pi.h/3)(R^2+r^2+Rr)\nScale by k: V->k^3, SA->k^2 | Melting: V stays same",
